            "id": "4575520",
            "title": "Alibaba reportedly launches AI model for games and video to challenge Tencent",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Alibaba Group (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BABA\" title=\"Alibaba Group Holding Limited\">BABA</a></span>) has unveiled a new AI model capable of creating games and generating realistic video simulations, broadening its AI offerings as it seeks to compete more directly with Tencent Holdings (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/TCEHY\" title=\"Tencent Holdings Limited\">TCEHY</a></span>) and commercialize the technology.</li>\n<li>The Chinese e-commerce firm on Thursday unveiled Happy Oyster, a so-called world model that can create 3D environments and interactive videos. It can be used to produce films, video content and games, the company said, according to a Bloomberg report.</li>\n<li data-end=\"189\" data-start=\"0\">\n<span class=\"whitespace-normal\">Last week Alibaba (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BABA\" title=\"Alibaba Group Holding Limited\">BABA</a></span></span>) </span>said it developed the “Happy Horse” video AI model, claiming the platform topped global rankings on its debut.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
