            "id": "4575530",
            "title": "Asian markets rise tracking Wall Street peaks on US-Iran peace hopes, tech gains, and China GDP beat",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Asian equity markets mostly rose on Thursday following a record rally on Wall Street due to hopes for renewed US-Iran negotiations and a long-term peace deal.<span> </span>Strong corporate earnings, a rise in technology shares, and resilience in the Chinese economy supported global gains.</p>\n<p><span>WTI crude futures traded steadily near $91 per barrel on Thursday.</span></p>\n<p><span>The benchmark KOSPI rose nearly 2% to around 6,200 on Thursday.</span></p>\n<p><span>Japan (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NKY:IND\" title=\"NIKKEI 225 Index\">NKY:IND</a>) rose 2.56% to trade above 59,000 on Thursday. The <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USD:JPY#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">Japanese yen</a> strengthened to around 158.8 per dollar on Thursday.</span><span></span></p>\n<p>China's (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SHCOMP\" title=\"SHANGHAI Index\">SHCOMP</a></span></span></span></span>) rose 0.55% <span>to above 4,000, hitting a fresh one-month high, while the Shenzhen Component Index climbed over 1.1% to 14,600 on upbeat domestic economic data</span><span>, and the </span><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/USD:CNY#source=url_first_level%3Amarket-news%7Csection%3Aglobal%7Csection_asset%3Afull_story%7Cbutton%3Abody_link\">offshore yuan</a><span> edged higher to above 6.81 per USD.</span></p>\n<p><span><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4575540-china-economic-growth-accelerates-to-50-in-q1-fastest-annual-pace-since-mid-2025\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"China’s economy grew by 5.0%\">China’s economy grew by 5.0%</a> year-on-year in Q1 2026, surpassing the 4.8% forecast and up from 4.5% the previous quarter. <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4575541-chinas-retail-sales-cool-to-17-as-unemployment-hits-13-month-high-despite-industrial-production-beat\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Industrial production increased by 5.7%\">Industrial production increased by 5.7%</a>, but retail sales rose only 1.7%, with the jobless rate at 5.4%.</span></p>\n<p><span>China’s industrial capacity utilization rate fell to 73.6 percent in the first quarter of 2026 from 74.1 percent in the same period a year earlier. China’s fixed-asset investment rose by 1.7% year-on-year in the first quarter of 2026, falling short of market expectations for a 1.9% increase.</span></p>\n<p><span>Hong Kong (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HSI\" title=\"Hang Seng Index\">HSI</a></span></span></span></span>) rose 1.60% to 26,160 on Thursday, extending gains for a third consecutive session.</span></p>\n<p><span></span>India (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SENSEX\" title=\"SENSEX Index\">SENSEX</a></span></span></span></span>)<span> </span><span>rose 0.32% to 78,420 on Thursday, extending gains for a second consecutive session. The Indian rupee hovered near 93.2 per dollar.</span></p>\n<p><span>China has become India's largest trading partner in 2025–26, surpassing the US, with bilateral trade between India and China at USD 151.1 billion, according to government data cited by the Economic Times.</span></p>\n<p>Australia (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AS51\">AS51</a>)<span> fell 0.29% to 8,999 in Thursday morning’s trade. The <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AUD:USD#hasComeFromMpArticle=false#source=section%3Amain_content%7Cbutton%3Abody_link%7Cfirst_level_url%3Anews\">Australian dollar</a> rose past $0.70, approaching levels not seen since June 2022.</span><span></span></p>\n<p><span>The jobless rate held steady at 4.3% in March, while employment increased by 17.9 thousand, driven entirely by full-time positions.</span></p>\n<p><span>Australia’s consumer inflation expectations climbed to 5.9% in April 2026 from 5.2% a month earlier.</span></p>\n<p><span>In the U.S. on Wednesday, a<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4575239-sp500-nasdaq-composite-dow-jones-wall-street\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"ll three major indexes ended mixed\">ll three major indexes ended higher,</a> led by gains in the tech sector.</span><span></span></p>\n<p><span>Looking ahead, investors are eyeing a new wave of corporate earnings on Thursday, including reports from Netflix, PepsiCo, and Charles Schwab.</span></p>\n<p><span></span>U.S. stock futures<span> edged higher on Thursday following a record-setting session for the S&amp;P 500 and Nasdaq Composite</span><span>:</span> Dow<span> +0.09%</span>; S&amp;P 500 +0.17%; Nasdaq<span> +0.34%</span>.</p>\n<p><span>On the data front, markets will monitor weekly jobless claims along with updates on March capacity utilization and industrial production.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Currencies:</strong> (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/JPY:USD\" title=\"Japanese Yen / US Dollar\">JPY:USD</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CNY:USD\" title=\"Chinese Yuan / US Dollar\">CNY:USD</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AUD:USD\" title=\"Australian Dollar / US Dollar\">AUD:USD</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INR:USD\" title=\"Indian Rupee / US Dollar\">INR:USD</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HKD:USD\" title=\"Hong Kong Dollar / US Dollar\">HKD:USD</a>), (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NZD:USD\" title=\"New Zealand Dollar / US Dollar\">NZD:USD</a>).</p>\n<h2>More on Asia's markets and economy:</h2>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
